              "originalPosition": 86,
              "body": "Mein Vorschlag: \r\n\r\n... in order to avoid security incidents like signature forgery [MCGREW], [NISTSP]. Therefore, for stateful HBS, a secure environment MUST be used for key generation and key management.\r\n\r\nNote that, in general, root CAs offer such a secure environment and the number of issued signatures (including signed certificates and CRLs) is often moderate due to the fact that many root CAs delegate OCSP services or the signing of end-entity certificates to other entities (such as subordinate CAs) that use non-stateful signature schemes for their signatures. Therefore, many root CAs should be able to handle the required state management, and stateful HBS are still a proper solution for usage there. \r\n\r\nHBS MAY also be used for subordinate CA certificates, but special and careful consideration MUST be taken into account for proper key management. HBS MUST NOT be used for end-entity certificates.",
              "createdAt": "2023-06-15T11:44:27Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-06-15T13:01:47Z"
            }
          ]
        },
